## Modular Monolith Architecture

This project is a modular monolith: a single deployable unit with well-defined internal module boundaries.

### Module rules

- Each module owns its own business logic and data access; no reaching into another module's internals
- Modules communicate via public interfaces or events — never by calling internal functions of another module
- Keep `shared/` or `common/` packages minimal; prefer duplicating small utilities over coupling modules

### Adding new features

- Identify which module owns the feature; add code there
- If a feature spans modules, introduce a new module or a thin orchestration layer
- Resist the temptation to add generic abstractions until the same pattern appears three times
